flow.descriptionCdata:
2daa61c4-e717-44c5-aea8-f9fdaf2edf61.12deb1f2-dace-4b7d-a802-c99220c810bc.prompt=HostName\: 2daa61c4-e717-44c5-aea8-f9fdaf2edf61.22a8547a-dc1a-4da6-8c8d-24f2abbf5ff7.description=
Runs an SSH command

Inputs\:
host - Hostname or ip address.
port - The port number for running the command. It overwrites the port given inside the host input -in a syntax like host\:port-, if this exists.
command - The command to execute.
arguments - The arguments to pass to the command.
pty - Whether to use pty (true, false. Default is false).
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host. on the RAS.
username - Username to connect as.
password - Password of user. If using a private key file this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
timeout - Time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete (optional, default 90 seconds).
characterSet - The characterSet name for input stream encoding from the target machine. For example, SJIS, EUC-JP, UTF-8.  By default it is UTF-8. 
closeSession - Close SSH session at completion of this operation (true, false)? If false the ssh session will be cached for future calls of this operation during the life of the flow. If true the ssh session used by this operation will be closed. Default is true.

Responses\:
success - The command was executed successfully.
failure - The command could not be executed.

Extra Results\:
STDERR - The STDERR of the command.
STDOUT - The STDOUT of the command.
2daa61c4-e717-44c5-aea8-f9fdaf2edf61.2986af90-6f3b-452c-b053-6cb4c030fdc4.prompt=Interface to query\: 2daa61c4-e717-44c5-aea8-f9fdaf2edf61.828b6b19-f1da-48da-acb8-825c724e381b.prompt=UserName\: 2daa61c4-e717-44c5-aea8-f9fdaf2edf61.description=
This flow uses the ifconfig command to retreive information for a network interface on a FreeBSD host. 


Inputs\:
host - Hostname or ip address.
interface - interface on the host to retreive information for. 
username - Username to connect as.
password - Password of user. If using a private key file, this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host. on the RAS.
port - The port which the ssh daemon is listening on host. Default 22. 
characterSet - The characterSet name for input stream encoding from the target machine. For example, SJIS, EUC-JP, UTF-8.  By default it is UTF-8. 
timeout - Time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete (optional, default 90 seconds).
closeSession - Close SSH session at completion of this operation (true, false)? 
	  If false the ssh session will be cached for future calls of the 
	  'SSH Command' operation during the life of the calling flow. 
	  If true the ssh session used by this operation will be closed.
	  Default\: true


Responses\:
success - the data was obtained
failure - the data could not be obtained

Extra Results\:
stdOut - STDOUT from ifconfig
flags - flags parsed from ifconfig
metric - metric parsed from ifconfig
mtu - mtu parsed from ifconfig
options - options parsed from ifconfig
macAddress - MAC address parsed from ifconfig
inetAddress - inet address parsed from ifconfig
inetNetmask - inet netmask parsed from ifconfig
inetBroadcast - inet broadcast parsed from ifconfig
inet6Address - inet6 address parsed from ifconfig
inet6PrefixLen - inet6 prefixlen parsed from ifconfig
inet6ScopeId - inet6 scopeid parsed from ifconfig
media - media parsed from ifconfig
status - status parsed from ifconfig
sessionId - If the closeSession input was false, this will contain the cached 
                  SSH sessionId for future use by the 'SSH Command' operation
flow.name: Interface Info
